nce in the 21st century. History plays a central role in important societal discourses. In order to continue to actively participate in the future, historians must identify, name, and productively address challenges and problems. This volume takes up the task.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aHistoriography. 0aHistoryxResearch. 4aGeschichtsdebatte. 4aGeschichtsdiskurs. 4aGeschichtsschreibung. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 7aHISTORY / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aHistorical debates.  ahistorical discourse.  ahistoriography.  ascience of history.1 aArendes, Cord, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDöring, Karoline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDöring, Karoline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemper, Claudia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKemper, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKönig, Mareike, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKönig, Mareike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLogge, Thorsten, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLogge, Thorsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiebold, Angela, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSiebold, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerheyen, Nina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVerheyen, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook pac